                <opener>
                    <dateline>Feb'y 15 1926-</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr <hi rend="caps">J.G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                
                        <addrLine>Branson, <hi rend="caps">MO.</hi></addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>My dear Doctor&#8212;</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>It is not from lack of appreciation that have not acknowledged your splendid "The Song of the Indian Wars"&#8212; It has given me many thrills, revived many memories that lay dormant in Time Pigeon holes&#8212;</p>
                
                <p>Your inscription of gratitude is <unclear>finally</unclear> reciprocating in behalf of <hi rend="caps">K</hi> Troop that stood and moved at command, and maybe halted a victor's rush on Reno hill&#8212;</p>
                
                <p>I had hoped to see you at our annual meeting and banquet of The Order of Indian Wars of which I am happy to <unclear>state</unclear> you are an Honorary Member. But when I learned of the death of our mutual friend, Major Lemley, I gave that expectation up &#8212; I <unclear>used</unclear> to see much of Lemly at the Army + Navy I <unclear>Club</unclear> and <unclear>last</unclear> saw him at Genl. Miles funeral he then seemed to be 
                
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.12.20-23_0002"/>
                    <fw type="curatorial">21</fw>
                
                    in good health and said he was enjoying his luxurious apartments at the Mayflower&#8212; the amendment to our Constitution admitting Honorary and Associate membership was strongly advocated by Lemly and always <unclear>he</unclear> you in mind as a candidate for admission&#8212;</p>
                
                <p>It was with some reluctance that I accepted the responsibilities as Chairman of the National Custer Memorial Association because of the work at long distance from Headquarters&#8212;:  However I accepted in the hope that this reunion would bring together Indian War Veterans of all Indian Wars and campaigns; all "Winners of the West," including Pioneers &#8212; I was glad of the privilege to name you as a member of the Committee &#8212;</p> 
                
                <p>Responses from many <unclear>quarters</unclear> indicate that there will probably be a big crowd.</p>
                
                <p>I feel considerable <unclear>concern</unclear> as to the <unclear>housing</unclear> or <unclear>caring</unclear>, in general of the Veterans, but hope our <del/>Congress will give us assistance, especially in <unclear/> and Troops, etc. that will be helpful to the old Veterans&#8212;</p>
                
                <p>I know that at the organization of the <hi rend="underline">Asn</hi> they mapped out a considerable program for <unclear>Congress</unclear> special stamps, Memorial building, transportation, etc. but the Economy program may defeat several of the items. And too perhaps
                
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.12.20-23_0003a"/>
                    <fw type="curatorial">22</fw>
                
                    the event itself may not seem sufficient by remote to appeal to the lawmakers. To my mind the States more particularly concerned should meet the local demands that are not of National relation &#8212;</p>
                
                <p>However I am not fully informed as to the legislative program to fund responsibility.</p> 
                
                <p>I have not heard from Mr. Shoemaker<unclear>'s</unclear> Sec'y for several weeks, but was informed that he was suddenly called away to his son's (sick) bedside&#8212;</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely and Cordially Yours</salute>
                
                    <signed>E.S. Godfrey</signed>
                    <note type="curatorial">Gen. <hi rend="caps">E.S.</hi> Godfrey</note>
                </closer>
      
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.12.20-23_0004"/>
